hey i'm working on this embedded c++ project for an automotive sensor module and we're seeing a slow memory leak. the heap just gradually drains over like 4-5 hours of runtime until it crashes. i dont see any obvious new/delete mismatches in the main loop. can u give me a systematic way to track down where the leak is coming from? 

here is the snippet for the logging buffer:

void log_event(const char* msg) {
    char* buffer = new char[256];
    strncpy(buffer, msg, 255);
    buffer[255] = '\0';
    event_queue.push(buffer);
}

looks okay at first glance but it's definitely eating RAM.

